Contest, Match
public class TieBreakMatch
extends SerialContest
implements Match

A tie-break match (for the purposes of this assignment) is one in which all the sets are tie-break sets. After a tie-break game (which ends a set), the first game of the next set, if any, is served by the player who did not serve first in the tie-break.
